<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01083b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01083b">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01083b"> 83(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> spike (casual ward) ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The real gipsy still lights a wood fire within his blanket tent and huddles up by the embers in the blinding fumes. Very few vagrants sleep out during the winter months. They resort to the &ldquo;<mark>spike</mark>&rdquo; or casual ward when they have not enough coppers to pay for a &ldquo;doss&rdquo; in the common lodging house. <small> <a name="DM28dec22" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DM28dec22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (28 December 1922) 6/5 [GIPSIES IN WINTER.]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05145h" href="c05all.htm#c05145h">VI.C.05:145(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
